CatDescriptText: Mrs. E. P. Tunie, 1300 Glenn Street, Homestead, was part of a man on the street column entitled "Amos 'n' Andy Television Show Offends Some, Pleases Others," published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1951, pg. 3
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. E.P. Tunie wearing light colored short sleeved blouse with squared lace trim, eyeglasses, and diamond patterned apron with figurative patterned pocket, standing in interior with floral wallpaper
